  "task": "Implement linearizable distributed consensus with Byzantine leader election, dynamic reconfiguration, and cryptographic state verification. Build on v6 by adding: (1) Linearizability proof — demonstrate all concurrent operations appear as single-threaded execution with total ordering; verify via trace analysis against linearization points; (2) Byzantine leader election — leader can be faulty; system must elect new leader, maintain safety during transition, tolerate 1/3 Byzantine nodes in election; (3) Dynamic reconfiguration — add/remove replicas at runtime; old and new quorum sizes must be safe (never allow single-quorum split-brain); (4) Merkle tree state verification — replicas compute cryptographic merkle trees of state; periodic verification detects divergence within 100ms; (5) Strict p99 latency under adversarial load — 500ms p99 with 30% Byzantine byzantine nodes actively delaying/dropping messages; (6) Log compaction with safe snapshotting — compress logs without losing safety; snapshots must include quorum signatures proving they were committed; (7) Total ordering verification — provide timestamped operation log that is identical across all correct replicas; agent must prove no causality violations.",
